dimensions.description:
The well-being thresholds in this dataset are different to the standard well-being thresholds that are published as part of this release. This is because the data for the anxiety measure needs to be interpreted differently to the other three well-being measures. For example, high happiness scores relate to a positive well-being, while high anxiety scores relate to a poor well-being.

The well-being thresholds used in this dataset map onto the thresholds used in the main publication in the following way:

- Poor = Low levels of life satisfaction, worthwhile, happiness and high levels of anxiety.
- Fair = Medium levels of life satisfaction, worthwhile, happiness and anxiety.
- Good = High levels of life satisfaction, worthwhile, happiness and low levels of anxiety.
- Very good = Very high levels of life satisfaction, worthwhile, happiness and very low levels of anxiety.
